<item>
            <title>[SOLR-5318] create command don&apos;t take into account the transient core property</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5318</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;the create core admin command don&apos;t take into account the transient core property, when the core is registered (so, the core will be never closed by the transient core cache)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To reproduce :&lt;br/&gt;
set transientCacheSize=2 and start with no cores&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Create 3 cores :&lt;br/&gt;
curl &quot;http://ip:port/solr/admin/cores?action=CREATE&amp;amp;name=coreX&amp;amp;instanceDir=path_to_instanceDir_coreX&amp;amp;dataDir=path_to_dataDir_coreX&amp;amp;loadOnStartup=false&amp;amp;transient=true&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Look at the status :&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://ip:port/solr/admin/cores?action=STATUS&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://ip:port/solr/admin/cores?action=STATUS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All cores are still loaded.&lt;br/&gt;
One core should not be loaded (closed by the transient cache)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch in attachment is for svn solr branch_4X (revision number 1526418)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
